SIMPLE: toilet
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Toilet
<hw>Toi"let</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>toilette</ets>, dim. of <ets>toile</ets> cloth. See <er>Toil</er> a
net.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A covering of linen, silk, or tapestry,
spread over a table in a chamber or a dressing room.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A dressing table.</def> <rj><au>Pope.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Act or mode of dressing, or that which is arranged
in dressing; attire; dress; <as>as, her <ex>toilet</ex> is
perfect</as>.</def> <altsp>[Written also
<asp>toilette</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Toilet glass</b></col>, <cd>a looking-glass for a toilet
table or for a dressing room.</cd> -- <mcol><col><b>Toilet
service</b></col>, <col><b>Toilet set</b></col></mcol>, <cd>earthenware,
glass, and other utensils for a dressing room.</cd> -- <col><b>Toilet
table</b></col>, <cd>a dressing table; a toilet. See def. 2 above.</cd>
-- <col><b>To snake one's toilet</b></col>, <cd>to dress one's self;
especially, to dress one's self carefully.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Toilette</ent>⟦br⟧
